  "title": "Interior Design Project Executive | 2 years Contract | Up to $3k + Bonus - 0310",
  "description": "<p><strong>Interior Design Project Executive [ 2 Years Contract ]</strong></p><ul><li><p>Salary: SGD 2,500–3,000 + Bonus</p></li><li><p>Working Hours: Monday–Friday: 9 AM–6 PM / Saturday: 9 AM–1 PM</p></li><li><p>Working days: 5.5-day work week</p></li><li><p>Work Address: Kaki Bukit, Singapore</p></li><li><p>Site Travelling Required [ Transport Allowance Provided ]</p></li></ul><p>Interested applicants can also send your resume to (Liwenpoh741#gmail.com) and allow our consultant to match you with our clients. No Charges will be incurred by Candidates for any service rendered.</p><p>WA ME <a href=\"tel:9735 4019\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>9735 4019</strong></a> for more Interior Designer role</p><p><em><strong>Job Scope</strong></em></p><ol><li><p><em><strong>Prepare quotations, material selections & pricing breakdowns</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Present proposals and assist Director in client meetings & deal closures</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Conduct site visits, liaise with contractors, and ensure progress updates</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Draft layout plans, elevations, reflected ceiling plans (RCP), and M&E drawings</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Create 3D visualisations and presentation visuals for client approval</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Produce technical and shop drawings for carpentry & joinery works</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Liaise with workshop, suppliers, clients, and relevant authorities</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Oversee on-site progress, report to Director, and ensure project compliance</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Handle documentation for safety, SFA, PUB, and submission forms when needed</strong></em></p></li></ol><p><em><strong>Software Required</strong></em></p><ul><li><p>Provide portfolio / link during application submission, 2 years contract for this post, renewable or convert to permanent based on performance.</p></li><li><p><em><strong>AutoCAD (must-have)</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>SketchUp / 3Ds Max / Lumion (for 3D visualisation)</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Photoshop / Canva / PowerPoint (for presentation materials)</strong></em></p></li><li><p><em><strong>Google Sheets / WhatsApp / Cloud Drive (for communication & documentation)</strong></em></p></li></ul><p>POH LI WEN REG NO: R25136683</p><p>THE SUPREMEHR ADVISORY PTE LTD EA NO: 14C7279</p>",
